<example xml:id="sample-GT1"><title>GT1</title>
<statement>
    <p>
Let <m>A</m> be a <m>4 \times 4</m> matrix with determinant <m>-7</m>.
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
Let <m>B</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m>R_3 \to R_3+3R_4</m>. What is <m>\det(B)</m>?
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
Let <m>C</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m>R_2 \to -3R_2</m>. What is <m>\det(C)</m>?
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
Let <m>D</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m>R_3 \leftrightarrow R_4</m>. What is <m>\det(D)</m>?
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</statement>
<solution>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
Adding a multiple of one row to another row does not change the determinant, so <m>\det(B)=\det(A)=-7</m>.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
Scaling a row scales the determinant by the same factor, so so <m>\det(B)=-3\det(A)=-3(-7)=21</m>.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
Swaping rows changes the sign of the determinant, so <m>\det(B)=-\det(A)=7</m>.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</solution>
</example>